  "texts": [
    "Similarly, there are trade-offs between a model's robustness and fairness guarantees [59].This section discusses white-box and black-box evasion attack techniques, attack transferability, and the potential mitigation of adversarial examples in more detail.",
    "White-Box Evasion AttacksThere are several optimization-based methods for designing evasion attacks that generate adversarial examples at small distances from the original testing samples.",
    "There are also several choices for distance metrics, universal evasion attacks, and physically realizable attacks, as well as examples of evasion attacks developed for multiple data modalities, including NLP, audio, video, and cybersecurity domains.Optimization-based methods.",
    "Szedegy et al. [287] and Biggio et al.",
    "[26] independently proposed the use of optimization techniques to generate adversarial examples."
  ]
}